17:00.896 --> 17:03.899
Oh, boy. There he is.

17:04.566 --> 17:06.902
That's the Mantivore.

17:07.653 --> 17:08.654
Aha!

17:08.737 --> 17:12.907
It appeared I had found my suspect,
the Mantivore.

17:12.991 --> 17:16.369
He just looked big
because of my magnifying glass.

17:24.127 --> 17:26.839
Okay, wow. You're actually big.

17:27.422 --> 17:30.259
You!

17:38.934 --> 17:42.604
If I want to give my tree the best spot,
then I'll do it.

17:42.688 --> 17:46.942
I am a Gorg. And I do what I want.

17:50.112 --> 17:52.948
Then why do I feel so lousy?

17:54.283 --> 17:56.368
No, no, no.

17:56.451 --> 17:58.203
Sorry, Junior Junior.

17:58.787 --> 18:03.500
I want the best for you,
but I can't hurt the other plants.

18:04.334 --> 18:08.172
It might not be perfect,
but it'll still be great.

18:08.255 --> 18:09.464
Sound good?

18:10.549 --> 18:11.550
Sure.

18:11.633 --> 18:16.180
Sure. As long as you keep
Leafy McBlooms-a-lot out of our way!

18:16.263 --> 18:17.264
Capoosh?

18:17.347 --> 18:19.016
Okay, capoosh.

18:19.558 --> 18:21.727
You still seem pretty angry.

18:21.810 --> 18:24.479
He did the right thing.
Give him some credit.

18:25.147 --> 18:28.025
Honestly,
it's not even completely about him.

18:28.108 --> 18:31.278
-I just-- I haven't been sleeping well.
-Uh-oh.

18:31.361 --> 18:34.198
You…

18:34.281 --> 18:36.867
are both welcome in my home.

18:36.950 --> 18:39.328
-What?
-Wai-- Wait.

18:39.411 --> 18:43.248
-You're welcoming us?
-Why'd you say it in such a scary way?

18:43.332 --> 18:46.376
You know…

18:46.460 --> 18:48.837
I never really thought
about it that way.

18:48.921 --> 18:50.339
It's just the way I talk.

18:51.632 --> 18:55.010
Do you think that's why
the Craggles are scared of me?

18:55.636 --> 18:58.222
I mean, it doesn't really help.

18:58.847 --> 19:02.976
Oh, all right.
Enough small talk and big scary talk.

19:03.060 --> 19:06.730
-Why did you take the water, Mantivore?
-Yeah.

19:06.813 --> 19:09.316
Oh, please, call me Manty.

19:09.399 --> 19:11.777
And I didn't take the water.

19:12.694 --> 19:14.238
Then who did?

19:14.321 --> 19:15.656
It was…

19:15.739 --> 19:17.741
you!

19:20.035 --> 19:22.120
I feel like I'm missing something.

19:22.204 --> 19:24.331
That's-- That's my hair tie.

19:24.414 --> 19:27.584
But how did it get all the way over here?

19:27.668 --> 19:30.671
The last time I lost a hair tie was…

19:31.547 --> 19:32.840
I got you, Gobo!

19:32.923 --> 19:36.552
We were looking for
Gobo's uncle's backpack and got trapped.

19:40.138 --> 19:43.642
We moved a boulder,
and then all this water came pouring out.

19:43.725 --> 19:46.395
-Is that…
-Water!

19:47.729 --> 19:49.940
We got blasted into these water slides,

19:50.023 --> 19:53.777
and it created a beautiful new waterfall
in our Great Hall.

19:57.197 --> 19:58.699
-Wow!
-Wow!

19:58.782 --> 20:01.285
Look at all of this new water!

20:01.368 --> 20:07.457
Yes, but did you ever think about
where all that water came from?

20:08.709 --> 20:13.380
They're going to blame
this on you, Manty.

20:14.256 --> 20:19.178
So, moving the boulder rerouted the water

20:19.261 --> 20:21.346
and made the lagoon dry up?

20:22.723 --> 20:27.477
I can't believe the suspect
I was looking for this whole time was…

20:28.187 --> 20:29.188
You.

20:30.522 --> 20:32.524
Wow, you said that so quietly.

20:32.608 --> 20:34.776
Well, I thought it fit the moment better.

20:41.366 --> 20:45.329
Wow, we really didn't have to go anywhere
to have a great time, huh?

20:45.412 --> 20:49.917
Other people might get fancy vacations,
but we're actually pretty lucky, Sprocket.

20:50.000 --> 20:52.794
I mean, look what we made work right here.

20:54.963 --> 20:56.340
Wait a minute.

20:57.007 --> 20:58.509
Right here.

20:58.592 --> 21:01.595
What's stopping me
from setting up a lab right here?

21:01.678 --> 21:05.807
I'll have to pull some extra power,
use some makeshift equipment.

21:06.558 --> 21:09.478
But who ever changed the world
by doing it the normal way?

21:10.687 --> 21:14.274
Sprocket, we are going to solve
the ocean's plastic problem.

21:14.358 --> 21:17.069
And we're gonna do it right here at home.

21:18.278 --> 21:19.279
Oh, don't worry.

21:19.363 --> 21:20.906
We can finish our camping trip first.

21:21.907 --> 21:23.200
You're sloshing it.

21:23.283 --> 21:25.202
-Got it? Hold it steady.
-I got it, Gobo. Okay.

21:26.203 --> 21:27.454
No sloshing.

21:27.538 --> 21:30.040
-I'll pour. I'll pour.
-I'm trying.

21:30.123 --> 21:33.252
You can't both pour.
Someone has to hold the bucket.

21:33.335 --> 21:34.795
-I'm trying.
-Yeah, I--

21:34.878 --> 21:36.964
They're sloshing. They're sloshing.

21:37.047 --> 21:39.341
Water flows. Flow with it.

21:39.424 --> 21:41.301
Well, how do you do that?

21:41.385 --> 21:46.974
Okay, everybody,
Inspector Red has solved the case.

21:47.057 --> 21:48.976
-All right.
-You did?

21:49.893 --> 21:51.270
What case?

21:52.020 --> 21:55.065
I thought we deserved a dumb vacation,

21:55.148 --> 22:00.821
when this whole time the Craggles
didn't have any water because of us.

22:00.904 --> 22:02.865
What? Well, what did we do?

22:02.948 --> 22:05.784
I'll explain everything later,
but for now,

22:05.868 --> 22:08.287
the Craggles are going to stay
here with us

22:08.370 --> 22:13.125
and have as much of our water
as they need while we figure things out.

22:14.251 --> 22:18.046
Thank goodness, 'cause our
bucket brigade is not going so well.

22:18.130 --> 22:19.381
Yeah, you were sloshing.

22:19.464 --> 22:21.717
-Okay, really?
-Great idea, Red.

22:21.800 --> 22:23.510
Yeah, Red. Wow.

22:23.594 --> 22:25.637
That's really thoughtful of you.

22:27.222 --> 22:30.350
I'm not liking
how surprised you sound by that.

22:32.561 --> 22:36.106
That's right. Bring that goo here.

22:37.524 --> 22:39.860
Dump it in and we'll mix it
with the Doozer sticks.

22:39.943 --> 22:43.822
All right, I'm back.
Time to work on my goo experiments.

22:43.906 --> 22:44.907
-Hooray!
-Yay!

22:44.990 --> 22:46.158
Yeah. All right.

22:46.241 --> 22:50.037
Cotterpin, congratulations
on discovering this sticky goo.

22:50.120 --> 22:52.873
Why, we've already put it into production.

22:52.956 --> 22:54.458
Goo.

22:54.541 --> 22:57.628
But I wasn't finished testing it.

22:57.711 --> 22:59.588
Oh, Cotterpin!

23:02.716 --> 23:06.261
We thought you deserved
some recognition for your work.

23:06.345 --> 23:08.013
-Yeah. That's right.
-Yeah.

23:08.096 --> 23:10.933
-So congrats. Congrats. Yeah.
-Congrats. Yeah.

23:11.016 --> 23:13.560
Great Doozer on a Snoozer!

23:19.107 --> 23:21.026
Well, I gotta hand it to you, Red.

23:21.109 --> 23:23.278
You did something great for the Craggles.

23:24.530 --> 23:27.950
I really took it for granted
how good we have it here.

23:29.326 --> 23:32.162
Maybe it's time
the Craggles got a vacation.

23:32.246 --> 23:33.705
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

23:33.789 --> 23:36.375
So, where do you see them staying?

23:36.458 --> 23:38.460
And what are we gonna do
about their water?

23:38.544 --> 23:40.420
Hey, who's gonna do their laundry?

23:41.004 --> 23:42.005
Don't worry.

23:42.089 --> 23:46.176
Red would've never brought the Craggles
here without thinking all that through.

23:46.260 --> 23:47.845
-Right, Red?
-Of course. Of course.

23:49.513 --> 23:51.265
What the gang did not know

23:51.348 --> 23:55.602
was that Inspector Red had not
thought any of that through.

23:58.146 --> 24:00.732
Again, we can hear you.

24:00.816 --> 24:01.817
Oh.
